annotation: <history><entry><input>touch "file1.txt"</input><output></output><annotation>The `touch` command creates an empty file named "file1.txt" in the current directory.</annotation></entry><entry><input>echo "This is the first file" > file1.txt</input><output></output><annotation>Writes the string "This is the first file" to the file "file1.txt".</annotation></entry><entry><input>cat file1.txt</input><output>This is the first file</output><annotation>The `cat` command displays the contents of "file1.txt" in the terminal.</annotation></entry><entry><input>touch "file2.txt"</input><output></output><annotation>The `touch` command creates an empty file named "file2.txt".</annotation></entry><entry><input>echo "This is the second file" > file2.txt</input><output></output><annotation>Writes the string "This is the second file" to the file "file2.txt".</annotation></entry><entry><input>cat file2.txt</input><output>This is the second file</output><annotation>The `cat` command displays the contents of "file2.txt" in the terminal.</annotation></entry><entry><input>diff file1.txt file2.txt</input><output>2c2  <  This is the first file  ---  > This is the second file</output><annotation>The `diff` command compares "file1.txt" and "file2.txt" and shows the differences between them.</annotation></entry><entry><input>cp file1.txt file1_copy.txt</input><output></output><annotation>The `cp` command creates a copy of "file1.txt" and names it "file1_copy.txt".</annotation></entry><entry><input>cat file1_copy.txt</input><output>This is the first file</output><annotation>The `cat` command displays the contents of the copied file, "file1_copy.txt".</annotation></entry><entry><input>mv file2.txt "moved_file.txt"</input><output></output><annotation>The `mv` command renames "file2.txt" to "moved_file.txt".</annotation></entry><entry><input>ls</input><output>file1.txt  file1_copy.txt  moved_file.txt</output><annotation>The `ls` command lists the contents of the current directory, showing the files "file1.txt", "file1_copy.txt", and "moved_file.txt".</annotation></entry><entry><input>rm moved_file.txt</input><output></output><annotation>The `rm` command deletes "moved_file.txt" from the current directory.</annotation></entry><entry><input>ls</input><output>file1.txt  file1_copy.txt</output><annotation>After deleting "moved_file.txt", the `ls` command shows only "file1.txt" and "file1_copy.txt" in the directory.</annotation></entry><entry><input>exit</input><output></output><annotation>The `exit` command ends the terminal session.</annotation></entry></history>
